[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1598},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":1575,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2023\u002F03\u002F30\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue\u002F":1584},"\u002Fvue\u002F20230330\u002F238425903\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1557,"date":1558,"description":19,"extension":1559,"lang":1560,"meta":1561,"navigation":470,"path":1562,"readingMinutes":1563,"seo":1564,"standalone":1565,"stem":1566,"tags":1567,"tldr":1572,"updated":1558,"url":1573,"__hash__":1574},"content\u002Fen\u002FVue\u002Fimporting-images-in-vue.md","How to Import Images in Vue (Vue CLI and Vite)","2985243003",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1539},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,33,43,56,100,111,118,139,142,168,171,197,200,204,210,234,240,243,285,288,318,328,331,335,338,355,360,370,618,636,667,670,674,679,705,708,712,715,741,744,802,808,815,841,844,868,872,883,900,907,933,939,965,973,985,989,992,1006,1010,1017,1130,1134,1137,1213,1217,1220,1234,1239,1315,1320,1396,1400,1410,1413,1419,1478,1481,1535],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"A quick note on how to import images properly in Vue CLI or Vite. It's a common question and easy to get wrong, so I figured I'd write it down.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"static-vs-non-static-assets","Static vs non-static assets",[17,25,26],{},"Before getting into the how, I want to explain what \"static\" and \"non-static\" assets actually mean.",[17,28,29],{},"Since I'll be talking about Vue CLI later, let me use Vue CLI as the example here.",[17,31,32],{},"Vue CLI is built on Webpack, so importing images breaks down into two categories:",[34,35,36,40],"ul",{},[37,38,39],"li",{},"Static assets",[37,41,42],{},"Non-static assets",[17,44,45,46,50,51,55],{},"What's a static asset? Remember the ",[47,48,49],"code",{},"public"," folder in a Vue CLI project? That folder is specifically for static assets — and by \"static\" I mean ",[52,53,54],"strong",{},"assets that don't go through Webpack bundling\u002Fcompilation",". So you can reference them directly in HTML:",[57,58,63],"pre",{"className":59,"code":60,"language":61,"meta":62,"style":62},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cimg src=\"\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png\" alt=\"logo\" \u002F>\n","html","",[47,64,65],{"__ignoreMap":62},[66,67,70,74,78,82,85,89,92,94,97],"span",{"class":68,"line":69},"line",1,[66,71,73],{"class":72},"sMAXC","\u003C",[66,75,77],{"class":76},"sKpQp","img",[66,79,81],{"class":80},"sCcAr"," src",[66,83,84],{"class":72},"=",[66,86,88],{"class":87},"sTRMh","\"\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png\"",[66,90,91],{"class":80}," alt",[66,93,84],{"class":72},[66,95,96],{"class":87},"\"logo\"",[66,98,99],{"class":72}," \u002F>\n",[17,101,102,103,106,107,110],{},"And your ",[47,104,105],{},"logo.png"," would live at ",[47,108,109],{},"public\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png",".",[17,112,113,114,117],{},"Non-static assets, on the other hand, are bundled\u002Fcompiled by Webpack, so you have to bring them in via ",[47,115,116],{},"import",":",[57,119,123],{"className":120,"code":121,"language":122,"meta":62,"style":62},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","import logo from '.\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png'\n","js",[47,124,125],{"__ignoreMap":62},[66,126,127,130,133,136],{"class":68,"line":69},[66,128,116],{"class":129},"sWyjQ",[66,131,132],{"class":72}," logo ",[66,134,135],{"class":129},"from",[66,137,138],{"class":87}," '.\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png'\n",[17,140,141],{},"Then in your HTML you'd use:",[57,143,145],{"className":59,"code":144,"language":61,"meta":62,"style":62},"\u003Cimg :src=\"logo\" alt=\"logo\" \u002F>\n",[47,146,147],{"__ignoreMap":62},[66,148,149,151,153,156,158,160,162,164,166],{"class":68,"line":69},[66,150,73],{"class":72},[66,152,77],{"class":76},[66,154,155],{"class":80}," :src",[66,157,84],{"class":72},[66,159,96],{"class":87},[66,161,91],{"class":80},[66,163,84],{"class":72},[66,165,96],{"class":87},[66,167,99],{"class":72},[17,169,170],{},"And the compiled output looks different from the static version:",[57,172,174],{"className":59,"code":173,"language":61,"meta":62,"style":62},"\u003Cimg src=\"\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.1a2b3c.png\" alt=\"logo\" \u002F>\n",[47,175,176],{"__ignoreMap":62},[66,177,178,180,182,184,186,189,191,193,195],{"class":68,"line":69},[66,179,73],{"class":72},[66,181,77],{"class":76},[66,183,81],{"class":80},[66,185,84],{"class":72},[66,187,188],{"class":87},"\"\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.1a2b3c.png\"",[66,190,91],{"class":80},[66,192,84],{"class":72},[66,194,96],{"class":87},[66,196,99],{"class":72},[17,198,199],{},"You'll see a path like that — that's the Webpack-bundled output path.",[12,201,203],{"id":202},"how-to-import-images","How to import images",[17,205,206,207,209],{},"Static assets are pretty straightforward — drop them in the ",[47,208,49],{}," folder and reference them directly:",[57,211,212],{"className":59,"code":60,"language":61,"meta":62,"style":62},[47,213,214],{"__ignoreMap":62},[66,215,216,218,220,222,224,226,228,230,232],{"class":68,"line":69},[66,217,73],{"class":72},[66,219,77],{"class":76},[66,221,81],{"class":80},[66,223,84],{"class":72},[66,225,88],{"class":87},[66,227,91],{"class":80},[66,229,84],{"class":72},[66,231,96],{"class":87},[66,233,99],{"class":72},[17,235,236,237,239],{},"SCSS and CSS work the same way — put the file in ",[47,238,49],{}," and reference it directly.",[17,241,242],{},"SCSS:",[57,244,248],{"className":245,"code":246,"language":247,"meta":62,"style":62},"language-scss shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast",".logo {\n  background-image: url('\u002Fimg\u002Flogo.png');\n}\n","scss",[47,249,250,258,279],{"__ignoreMap":62},[